If you are reading this from the future, and using Navigation Component, this is a declarative way (automatically) to update the bottom icons when page is getting changed.

Based on this documentation [Update UI components with NavigationUI][1].
Unless Google made any change again

**First**, [Tie destinations to menu items][2]

it means, just provide android:id attribute&#39;s value to MenuItem same as the fragment of your \&lt;navigation&gt;&#39;s children

In the menu/your_menu_file.xml


&lt;!-- language: lang-xml --&gt;

    &lt;menu&gt;
      &lt;item
        android:id=&quot;@+id/navigation__fragment_home&quot;
        android:title=&quot;@string/example_label_nav_home&quot;/&gt;
        
      &lt;item
        android:id=&quot;@+id/navigation__fragment_about&quot;
        android:title=&quot;@string/example_label_nav_about&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/menu&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

In the navigation/your_navigation_file.xml

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;navigation&gt;
      &lt;fragment
        android:id=&quot;@+id/navigation__fragment_home&quot;
        tools:layout=&quot;@layout/fragment_page_home&quot;/&gt;
        
      &lt;fragment
        android:id=&quot;@+id/navigation__fragment_about&quot;
        tools:layout=&quot;@layout/fragment_page_about&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/navigation&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

**Second**, get the `NavHostFragment` to retrieve `NavController`
[based on this doc][3]

&lt;!-- language: lang-java --&gt;

    NavHostFragment navHostFragment =
            (NavHostFragment) getSupportFragmentManager().findFragmentById(R.id.your_FragmentContainerView);
    NavController navController = navHostFragment.getNavController();

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;
Better to place and save the `navHostFragment` and `navController` to the activity class, so you can reuse it.

**Last**, call setupWithNavController() for your `BottomNavigationView` (this is also for top app bar), [based on this doc][1]


&lt;!-- language: lang-java--&gt;

    BottomNavigationView bottomNav = findViewById(R.id.bottom_nav);
    NavigationUI.setupWithNavController(bottomNav, navController);

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

Now, actually you don&#39;t have to listen to any click event of the BottomNavigationView and back button event.
 
`BottomNavigationView` would automatically change the selected item, including navigation.


  [1]: https://developer.android.com/guide/navigation/navigation-ui
  [2]: https://developer.android.com/guide/navigation/navigation-ui#Tie-navdrawer
  [3]: https://developer.android.com/guide/navigation/navigation-getting-started#navigate
  [4]: https://developer.android.com/guide/navigation/navigation-getting-started#bottom_navigation

