This isn&#39;t necessarily a good idea. `toString()` should be used solely for debugging purposes: toString demands nothing of implementations, not even that they are consistent. Most things I can think of that would lead one to ask this question are problematic.

&gt; How can I override the `toString()` method of `Queue` class to get the correct output ?

